<TITLE> Riquelme ineligible for Club World Cup says FIFA </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, Nov 30 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Argentina's Juan Roman Riquelme cannot play for Boca Juniors in the Club World Cup next month, FIFA said on Friday. Riquelme had hoped his return to Boca from Spanish club Villarreal, sealed on Thursday in Buenos Aires, would give him the chance of playing in the tournament in Japan. However, the Argentina midfielder's transfer was too late for his inclusion in Boca's squad for the seven-team Dec. 7-16 tournament by the Nov. 23 deadline. "FIFA can confirm that the Argentina playmaker will not be eligible to take part in the forthcoming FIFA Club World Cup in Japan," world soccer's governing body said in a statement on its Web site (www.fifa.com). Riquelme played a key role in Boca's qualification for the tournament, inspiring them to their sixth South American Libertadores Cup title earlier this year while on loan from Villarreal
